Trips by purpose in the Hamilton CMA.

Source: R/envsocty3LT3-package.R
hamilton_trips_purpose.Rd

A table with information from the Transportation Tomorrow Survey regarding trips by purpose by traffic analysis zone. These data are for 2016.

data(hamilton_trips_purpose)

Format

A data frame with 297 rows and 26 variables:

GTA06

Unique identifier of zone in the GTA06 system

Unknown

Number of trips that originated in the traffic analysis zone for purpose: Unknown

Subsequent_School

Number of trips that originated in the traffic analysis zone for purpose: Subsequent_School

Daycare

Number of trips that originated in the traffic analysis zone for purpose: Daycare

Facilitate_passenger

Number of trips that originated in the traffic analysis zone for purpose: Facilitate_passenger

Home

Number of trips that originated in the traffic analysis zone for purpose: Home

Market_Shop

Number of trips that originated in the traffic analysis zone for purpose: Market_Shop

Other

Number of trips that originated in the traffic analysis zone for purpose: Other

Subsequent_Work

Number of trips that originated in the traffic analysis zone for purpose: Subsequent_Work

School

Number of trips that originated in the traffic analysis zone for purpose: School

Work

Number of trips that originated in the traffic analysis zone for purpose: Work

Source

Transportation Tomorrow Survey (http://dmg.utoronto.ca/transportation-tomorrow-survey/tts-introduction)

 data(hamilton_trips_purpose)
